JOHANNESBURG – The Naspers Group's annual profit increased by 72 percent for the year ended March 2018 The group's solid performance was helped largely by its stake in Tencent. READ: Naspers considers minorities buyout Naspers, which owns about 30- percent of the Chinese technology firm, says its headline earnings reached $2-billion. The group says businesses outside South Africa contributed 84 percent of revenues, compared to 80 percent a year ago. eNCA